{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2012}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Bobbie Bruce | fullname = | height = {{height|ft=5|in=6}}<ref name=moss>{{cite web|url=http://www.mossleyweb.com/MwebFrameset0809.htm|title=The Mossley Managers|publisher=Mossley AFC|accessdate=11 February 2010|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100318104154/http://www.mossleyweb.com/MwebFrameset0809.htm|archivedate=18 March 2010|df=dmy-all}}</ref> | birth_date = 29 January 1906<ref name=moss/> | birth_place = [[Paisley, Renfrewshire|Paisley]], Scotland | death_date = {{death year and age|1978|1906}} | position = [[forward (association football)|Inside left]] | youthyears1= | youthclubs1= [[St Anthony's F.C.|St Anthony's]] | years1=1924–1928|clubs1= [[Aberdeen F.C.|Aberdeen]]|caps1=93 |goals1=36 | years2=1928–1935|clubs2= [[Middlesbrough F.C.|Middlesbrough]]|caps2= |goals2= | years3=1935–1936|clubs3= [[Sheffield Wednesday F.C.|Sheffield Wednesday]]|caps3=5 |goals3= | years4=1936–1938|clubs4= [[Ipswich Town F.C.|Ipswich Town]]|caps4= |goals4= | years5=1938–1939|clubs5= [[Mossley A.F.C.|Mossley]]|caps5= |goals5= | manageryears1=1938–1939|managerclubs1=[[Mossley A.F.C.|Mossley]] | nationalyears1=1933|nationalteam1=[[Scotland national football team|Scotland]]|nationalcaps1=1|nationalgoals1=0 }} '''Robert Bruce''' (29 January 1906 – 1978)<ref name = "scotland">{{cite web |url=http://www.londonhearts.com/scotland/players/robertbruce.html |title=Robert Bruce |work=www.londonhearts.com |publisher=London Hearts Supporters' Club |date= |accessdate=8 June 2013}}</ref> was a Scottish [[Association football|footballer]]. He was born in [[Paisley, Renfrewshire|Paisley]].
An inside left who developed with the [[Glasgow|Glaswegian]] junior side St. Anthony's, Bruce spent his senior career with [[Aberdeen F.C.|Aberdeen]] (1924–1928), [[Middlesbrough F.C.]] (1928–1935), [[Sheffield Wednesday F.C.]] (1935–1936), and [[Ipswich Town F.C.]] (1936–1938). His last club was [[Mossley F.C.]], where he held the role of player-manager during the 1938–39 season. He played once for the [[Scotland national football team|Scottish national team]], against [[Austria national football team|Austria]] in 1933.<ref name = "scotland"/>
