'''Edward M. Bowman''' was a member of the [[Dakota Territory]] House of Representatives and the namesake of [[Bowman County, North Dakota]]. Bowman served the southern part of the territory during the 1883 legislative session, during which the county was established.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://genealogytrails.com/ndak/bowman/|title=Bowman County, North Dakota|publisher=Genealogy Trails|accessdate=September 10, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rootsweb.ancestry.com/~ndtttp/bowman/index.htm|title=Bowman County North Dakota|publisher=RootsWeb|accessdate=September 10, 2017}}</ref>

