A '''pet-raising simulation''' (sometimes called '''[[digital pet|artificial pets]]'''<ref name="ongamedesign">{{cite book|last=Rollings|first=Andrew|authorlink=|author2=Ernest Adams |title=Andrew Rollings and Ernest Adams on Game Design|publisher=New Riders Publishing|year=2003|location=|pages=477–487|url=http://safari.adobepress.com/1592730019/ch16|doi=|id=|isbn=1-59273-001-9}} </ref>) is a [[video game]] that focuses on the care, raising, breeding or exhibition of simulated animals. These games are software implementations of [[digital pet]]s. Such games are described as a sub-class of [[life simulation game]]. The concept originated from [[role-playing video game]]s, with the ''[[Megami Tensei]]'' series and ''[[Dragon Quest V: Hand of the Heavenly Bride|Dragon Quest V]]'' being the earliest examples.<ref>{{cite web|author=Oleg Roschin|title=The World of Asian RPGs: Brief History of Japanese RPGs|publisher=[[MobyGames]]|url=http://www.mobygames.com/featured_article/feature,25/section,168|accessdate=2009-09-10}}</ref>
